article_title: Brazilian Banking Magnate Moise Yacoub Safra Dies
article_text:
SAO PAULO—One of Brazil's wealthiest men, banker Moise Yacoub Safra died Sunday in São Paulo. He was 79. One of the founders of Brazilian bank Banco Safra, the magnate suffered from Parkinson's Disease, according to the local press.

Representatives at Banco Safra and Hospital Albert Einstein, where Mr. Safra was being treated, were not available...
